43
00:06:50,702 --> 00:06:53,413
Dragged topside
and thrown overboard.

44
00:06:55,707 --> 00:06:59,670
The two men in custody surrendered
after a brief attempt to escape.

45
00:06:59,711 --> 00:07:02,881
What do we know about them?
The men in custody?

46
00:07:05,759 --> 00:07:09,680
HaIf a dozen arrests for drug
trafficking in Bogota, Mr President.

47
00:07:10,764 --> 00:07:12,140
Drugs.

48
00:07:14,768 --> 00:07:17,771
Suspected ties to the Cali cartel,
not Medellin...

49
00:07:17,771 --> 00:07:20,858
- You all right, James?
- ...according to DEA.

50
00:07:21,733 --> 00:07:24,111
- Why?
- Nothing exotic, sir.

51
00:07:24,736 --> 00:07:28,073
Straight piracy and murder.
It's not the first time.

52
00:07:29,741 --> 00:07:32,744
It's the first time
it was a friend of mine.

53
00:07:34,746 --> 00:07:36,248
Yes, sir.

54
00:07:43,797 --> 00:07:46,592
- What was that? You all right?
- Yeah.

55
00:07:47,801 --> 00:07:49,803
I haven't slept in 36 hours.
Did I make any sense?

56
00:07:49,803 --> 00:07:52,681
What did you say?
Just kidding. Good job.

57
00:07:55,809 --> 00:07:59,980
- You should give diplomacy lessons.
- To call it as I see it is my job.

58
00:08:01,815 --> 00:08:04,276
- And he's yours.
- Wait for me.

59
00:08:08,780 --> 00:08:10,490
Shut the door.

60
00:08:14,786 --> 00:08:18,916
I promised the American people I'd
do something about the drug problem.

61
00:08:19,791 --> 00:08:21,251
You are.

62
00:08:21,793 --> 00:08:25,380
We support the Colombians' efforts
against the cartels...

63
