thing, and there's no response ever?

65
00:08:38,852 --> 00:08:41,813
Are you suggesting
a course of action, sir?

66
00:08:42,856 --> 00:08:46,944
The course of action I'd suggest is
a course of action I can't suggest.

67
00:09:03,836 --> 00:09:06,547
I'm...not sure
where that leaves us.

68
00:09:10,884 --> 00:09:14,429
These drug cartels represent
a clear and present danger -

69
00:10:56,949 --> 00:10:59,117
Come after me? Arrest me?

70
00:10:59,952 --> 00:11:01,828
You're scaring me.

71
00:11:03,956 --> 00:11:07,835
Will you stop long enough for me
to tell you something important?

72
00:11:11,004 --> 00:11:12,548
Thank you.

73
00:11:16,009 --> 00:11:19,763
Listen... You pay me to counsel you,
and I am counselling you.

74
00:11:22,015 --> 00:11:24,810
I'm keeping you alive
with information.

75
00:11:26,019 --> 00:11:30,148
If you disregard my counsel and keep
running your business like this, -

76
00:11:31,984 --> 00:11:35,654
- with your balls and not your head,
two things will happen.

77
00:11:36,989 --> 00:11:39,491
I'll quit, and you'll get killed.

78
00:11:52,004 --> 00:11:55,174
You forgot to tell me
about your scouting trip.

79
00:11:56,049 --> 00:11:59,219
- No, I didn't.
- You made another contact. Who?

80
00:12:01,054 --> 00:12:03,891
Castro always asked me
about my sources.

81
00:12:04,057 --> 00:12:08,228
- I always gave him the same answer.
- Castro didn't pay you what I pay.

82
00:12:10,063 --> 00:12:12,482
This one will cost you nothing.

83
00:12:15,027 --> 00:12:16,486
A woman.

84
00:12:17,029 --> 00:12:19,031
You're using a woman.

85
00:12:29,041 --> 00:12:32,002
- John, what do you want? Toast?
- Waffles!

86
00:12:32,044 --> 00:12:35,172
- No time for waffles.
- Anybody seen my keys?

87
00:12:36,089 --> 00:12:39,009
On the front hall table
or in your pocket.

88
00:12:39,092 --> 00:12:41,595
- Where are my keys?
- Pancakes!

89
00:12:42,095 --> 00:12:44,473
- Toast, please!
- Thank you.

90
00:12:46,099 --> 00:12:48,477
- Bye, pal.
- lt won't float!

91
00:12:49,102 --> 00:12:53,023
It's not supposed to float,
it's a submarine. lt goes under water.

92
00:12:58,070 --> 00:12:59,446
Hello?

93
00:13:02,074 --> 00:13:03,408
When?

94
00:13:05,077 --> 00:13:07,204
I thought I had the flu.

95
00:13:08,080 --> 00:13:11,583
I'd stilI think so if they weren't
telling me otherwise.

96
00:13:14,086 --> 00:13:16,338
What are they telling you?

97
00:13:18,131 --> 00:13:22,010
Pancreatic cancer of an aggressive
nature, if I heard them right.

98
00:13:24,137 --> 00:13:26,265
Well, what does it mean?

99
00:13:28,141 --> 00:13:30,769
I guess it means I'm in big trouble.

100
00:13:31,144 --> 00:13:34,064
- I mean, can they operate, or..?
- Maybe.

101
00:13:36,149 --> 00:13:40,529
That's what they said, "maybe", which
sounds suspiciously like "no" to me.

102
00:13:41,113 --> 00:13:43,240
There's one of them now.

103
00:13:46,118 --> 00:13:48,162
Hey, I'm not dead yet.

104
00:13:50,122 --> 00:13:53,792
I am in a hospital, which means
that I'm not in my office, -

105
00:13:56,128 --> 00:13:59,131
- which means
I don't know what's going on.

106
00:13:59,173 --> 00:14:01,175
- I need you there.
- Where?

107
00:14:01,175 --> 00:14:04,344
- In my office, doing my job.
- Wait a minute...

108
00:14:05,179 --> 00:14:08,432
I hate not knowing
what's going on, you know that.

109
00:14:09,183 --> 00:14:12,019
I wouldn't know
how to do your job, sir.

110
00:14:12,186 --> 00:14:15,480
You've been around.
You've been to the White House.

111
00:14:17,191 --> 00:14:19,860
- Once. I hated it.
- No, you didn't.

112
00:14:22,154 --> 00:14:25,657
Want to know about politics
in Washington? Four words...

113
00:14:26,158 --> 00:14:28,368
"Watch your back, Jack."

114
00:14:33,165 --> 00:14:37,044
Bobby, you should be the first
to know, or the third or fourth...

115
00:14:39,213 --> 00:14:42,216
Ryan is to be acting
Deputy Director of lntelligence.

116
00:14:42,216 --> 00:14:46,303
lt will be a provisional appointment,
of course, until James recovers.

117
00:14:48,222 --> 00:14:51,350
You brief him
on our aid programme to Colombia.

118
00:14:52,226 --> 00:14:56,355
He must talk the oversight committee
out of another 75 million dollars.

119
00:14:57,231 --> 00:15:00,192
And not make a complete fool
out of himself.

120
00:15:02,194 --> 00:15:04,571
What about the Hardin murders?

121
00:15:05,197 --> 00:15:08,784
I'm on it. The President's calling
for a full-court press.

122
00:15:09,201 --> 00:15:12,830
So, you guys are going to be
working together hand in hand.

123
00:15:15,207 --> 00:15:16,875
That's great.

124
00:15:32,266 --> 00:15:35,269
Margaret, why don't we
leave all his things?

125
00:15:50,242 --> 00:15:52,452
Ryan. I can't believe it !

126
00:15:53,245 --> 00:15:56,540
He's not a team player,
is that what you're saying?

127
00:15:57,249 --> 00:15:59,084
He's a Boy Scout.

128
00:16:00,252 --> 00:16:04,381
A god-damn Boy Scout. Believes in
loyalty, cleanliness and knot-tying.

129
00:16:06,300 --> 00:16:08,302
So leave him out of it.

130
00:16:08,302 --> 00:16:12,055
He's the Deputy Director of
lntelligence. That will be tricky.

131
00:16:12,306 --> 00:16:14,516
What does he need to know?

132
00:16:15,309 --> 00:16:19,062
Nothing. He needs to know nothing.
He's going to know nothing.

133
00:16:22,316 --> 00:16:25,277
I want a copy
of the President's authorisation -

134
00:16:25,277 --> 00:16:28,155
- of this new action
against the cartels.

135
00:16:29,281 --> 00:16:31,783
- You want what?
- You heard me.

136
00:16:34,286 --> 00:16:36,455
He doesn't know about it.

137
00:16:37,289 --> 00:16:41,210
Let me explain it to you very simply.
This is your deal. Not mine.

138
00:16:44,338 --> 00:16:48,550
Unless I have written authorisation,
this thing is over before it begins.

139
00:16:49,343 --> 00:16:53,639
I'm not going to be the only one left
without a chair when the music stops.

140
00:17:34,388 --> 00:17:37,432
"Reciprocity".
That's a clever name for it.

141
00:17:38,392 --> 00:17:41,687
Revenge is a very, very,
very dangerous motivation.

142
00:17:44,398 --> 00:17:48,610
Are you able to handle this operation
or not? I'm looking for a yes or no.

143
00:17:50,362 --> 00:17:52,990
You're looking for a political mess.

144
00:17:53,365 --> 00:17:56,118
- Yes or no?
- ls that what they want?

145
00:17:56,368 --> 00:18:00,372
They want what every first term
administration wants. A second term.

146
00:18:02,374 --> 00:18:05,878
I don't imagine the boys on the Hill
have approved this.

147
00:18:06,378 --> 00:18:08,255
The bill, please!

148
00:18:11,425 --> 00:18:12,968
Have they?

149
00:18:15,429 --> 00:18:17,264
ls that a "no"?

150
00:18:23,437 --> 00:18:24,771
Shit.

151
00:18:26,440 --> 00:18:29,776
I want the money in my account
before I move an inch.

152
00:18:31,403 --> 00:18:34,156
- You got it.
- I need a Com Sat link.

153
00:18:35,407 --> 00:18:38,494
- An insertion team.
- You can have a brigade.

154
00:18:39,411 --> 00:18:43,207
Just 1 2 men who understand
discretionary warfare. Special Ops.

155
00:18:53,467 --> 00:18:55,469
- How are you today, sir?
- Very well.

156
00:18:55,469 --> 00:18:58,305
- The purpose of your visit?
- Business.

157
00:18:59,473 --> 00:19:02,476
- What business are you in?
- I sell tractors.

158
00:19:02,476 --> 00:19:05,145
Well, I build them, then I sell them.

159
00:19:05,479 --> 00:19:08,690
- And how long will you be staying?
- A few days.

160
00:19:37,511 --> 00:19:40,639
I know it's a risk,
but what's the alternative?

161
00:19:41,515 --> 00:19:45,394
Zapping a retina with 6,000 rads
of cobalt? Not a pretty picture.

162
00:19:46,520 --> 00:19:49,523
Prettier than a tumour
spreading in the cranial sack.

163
00:19:49,523 --> 00:19:51,358
What is her name?

164
00:19:53,485 --> 00:19:55,320
Listen... Hungry?

165
00:19:57,489 --> 00:20:00,367
- Starved.
- We could forget about lunch.

166
00:20:01,493 --> 00:20:05,122
- We did that last time, remember?
- Do I remember? Do you?

167
00:20:08,500 --> 00:20:11,670
- Vaguely.
- Maybe I should refresh your memory.

168
00:20:14,548 --> 00:20:17,551
- Maybe you should.
- Your table is ready now.

169
00:20:17,551 --> 00:20:20,554
- We don't need it. I'll get a cab.
- Moira?

170
00:20:20,554 --> 00:20:24,057
- Hi! How are you? How's Jack?
- He's great, just great.

171
00:20:26,560 --> 00:20:29,563
- You still with the FBl?
- The Director's office.

172
00:20:29,563 --> 00:20:32,065
- Who was that?
- My new friend.

173
00:20:32,566 --> 00:20:34,526
Senor Roberto Landa.

174
00:20:35,527 --> 00:20:39,114
- Doesn't he look like Jack?
- Does he? I can't quite see.

175
00:20:39,531 --> 00:20:42,743
- Only Latin.
- A Latin Jack? This I have to see.

176
00:20:45,537 --> 00:20:47,414
I have to go. Bye.

177
00:20:49,541 --> 00:20:52,836
Well, we know it's not piracy.
Pirates steal boats.

178
00:20:54,588 --> 00:20:58,425
They had plane tickets to Bogota
the morning after the killings.

179
00:20:59,593 --> 00:21:01,595
- Hey, Dan.
- How's it going?

180
00:21:01,595 --> 00:21:04,598
We're sneaking up on a motive.
Dan Murray, FBl.

181
00:21:04,598 --> 00:21:07,559
- Ralph Williams, DEA.
- Said anything yet?

182
00:21:07,601 --> 00:21:11,396
- Yeah, "we're innocent".
- Till the D.A. offers them a deal.

183
00:21:12,606 --> 00:21:15,442
He already has.
Regular or extra crispy?

184
00:21:15,567 --> 00:21:19,071
Either referring to fried chicken
or the electric chair.

185
00:21:20,572 --> 00:21:22,574
Are you picturing a hit?

186
00:21:22,574 --> 00:21:25,953
On a respectable American
businessman and his family?

187
00:21:27,579 --> 00:21:30,082
You're assuming he's respectable.

188
00:21:38,632 --> 00:21:41,844
We have memos,
letters, credit card statements...

189
00:21:44,638 --> 00:21:48,225
...phone bills, anything
you could need to break his code.

190
00:21:50,644 --> 00:21:53,564
- What's this?
- Old high school yearbook.

191
00:21:53,647 --> 00:21:56,650
- Sweethearts, football team...
- You think?

192
00:21:57,609 --> 00:22:00,737
- I don't know.
- OK, let's see what we've got.

193
00:22:02,614 --> 00:22:05,075
- No cream?
- There wasn't any.

194
00:22:05,617 --> 00:22:09,413
Let's start with birthdays.
Bet your ATM code is your birthday.

195
00:22:09,621 --> 00:22:11,707
- Close.
- In reverse?

196
00:22:14,626 --> 00:22:16,962
All right, his birthday is...

197
00:22:18,672 --> 00:22:22,134
That would be too easy, wouldn't it?
Try it in reverse.

198
00:22:23,677 --> 00:22:25,429
No. His wife's?

199
00:22:27,681 --> 00:22:29,391
No. His son's?

200
00:22:29,683 --> 00:22:31,685
- This could take...
- Months.

201
00:22:31,685 --> 00:22:34,271
Son's in reverse.
This is for you.

202
00:22:36,690 --> 00:22:38,734
No. Wife's in reverse.

203
00:22:39,651 --> 00:22:41,653
No. Daughter's in reverse.

204
00:22:41,653 --> 00:22:44,239
You've got to change your ATM code.

205
00:22:54,666 --> 00:22:56,168
I got it!

206
00:23:06,720 --> 00:23:09,848
Wife's birth month,
daughter's day, son's year.

207
00:23:10,724 --> 00:23:12,935
But not in reverse. Sorry.

208
00:23:20,692 --> 00:23:23,153
Print me out that one, will you?

209
00:23:24,696 --> 00:23:26,198
Good boy.

210
