219
00:24:07,739 --> 00:24:09,032
Who?

220
00:24:09,741 --> 00:24:12,578
- His partners.
- Who were his partners?

221
00:24:12,744 --> 00:24:17,040
lt seems clear that he was laundering
money for the Colombian drug cartels.

222
00:24:19,751 --> 00:24:23,672
Jesus... I knew the man for 40 years.
We went to school together.

223
00:24:26,800 --> 00:24:29,553
We almost went
into business together.

224
00:24:29,803 --> 00:24:32,014
That would have been good.

225
00:24:33,807 --> 00:24:36,810
The press is going to
have a field-day with this.

226
00:24:36,810 --> 00:24:40,564
- No one outside this room knows.
- They will. They always do.

227
00:24:41,815 --> 00:24:45,777
lt will come up, you're right
about that. And when it does, we'll...

228
00:24:46,778 --> 00:24:50,032
...downplay your relationship
with Hardin somehow.

229
00:24:53,785 --> 00:24:55,579
- What?
- What?

230
00:24:55,787 --> 00:24:58,499
- We'll defuse it.
- Do you disagree?

231
00:24:59,791 --> 00:25:00,792
No.

232
00:25:00,792 --> 00:25:04,254
Well, actually, yes.
I would go in the other direction.

233
00:25:06,840 --> 00:25:11,220
If a reporter asked if you and Hardin
were friends, I'd say "good friends".

234
00:25:11,845 --> 00:25:15,891
If they asked if you were good
friends, I'd say "lifelong friends".

235
00:25:16,850 --> 00:25:20,270
Give them no place to go,
nothing to report. No story.

